# Lebanese flan or Mhalbi
<p align="center">
<img src="example.png" />
</p>

Preparation:  15mins  
Author:  
<a href="https://discord.com"><img src="https://img.shields.io/badge/Discord-saint_agughhh%234122-25?style=for-the-badge&logo=discord" /> </a> 


## Ingredients
<ul>
<li>250mL milk<li/>
<li>17g sugar<li/>
<li>15g maizena<li/>
<li>1 tablespoon orange flower water<li/>
<li>Honey, lemon juice, pistachios<li/>
<ul/>

## Materials
<ul>
<li>1 pot<li/>
<li>1 pretty glass<li/>
<ul/>

## Method
1. Dilute maizena in a bit of cold milk
2. Add milk and maizena in a casserole and bring to a boil. Mix until thick
3. Pour in glasses and let rest for 1h30mins in fridge
4. Mix honey and lemon juice together. Add on top with some crushed pistachios
## Conclusion
This recipe is relatively easy and will make a nice fancy dessert to accompany your dinner :)
